                                IconEdit

        IconEdit enables you to change the appearance of icons and create
new ones. You open IconEdit by double-clicking on it. The window that
appears shows a magnified view box in which you can edit or draw an icon.
To the right are the colour selection gadgets and various other gadgets
which help you draw, such as Freehand, Circle, Box and Line. You can import
IFF images created with other paint and draw programs to use as icons.

        Use the Project Menu to open an existing file for editing, create a
new icon file and save the file to disk. You use the type Menu to specify
the type of icon you're creating or editing - Disk, Drawer, Tool , Project
or Garbage (Trashcan). You can also determine how the icon will look when
it's selected using the Highlight Menu and Selected gadget to the right of
the window.

        For a full description of how to create and edit icons using
IconEdit, consult your Amiga Workbench user guide.




